ions of an idealized world-one without hunger, war, racism, and class oppression.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAfrican American authorsvCorrespondence. 0aAfrican American authorsxCorrespondence. 0aAuthors, AmericanxCorrespondencex20th century. 0aAuthors, Americany20th centuryvCorrespondence. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aCrawford, Evelyn Louise, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPatterson, MaryLouise, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520960862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520960862.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles